<TITLE> Sporting through as Derlei strike sinks Shakhtar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LISBON, Nov 5 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Sporting earned a place in the last 16 of the Champions League for the first time with a nervy 1-0 win over Shakhtar Donetsk on Tuesday. With two rounds remaining, Sporting moved to nine points in Group C a point behind leaders Barcelona, who also progress after a 1-1 draw with Basel. After a lacklustre first half with few chances for both teams, Sporting broke the deadlock when veteran Brazilian striker Derlei converted a cross from the Russian midfielder Marat Izmailov after 73 minutes. Sporting improved in the second half and Brazilian Liedson, who scored the only goal in the reverse fixture in Ukraine two weeks ago, wasted a golden chance when he fired wide after 66 minutes. Derlei then hit the decisive strike only four minutes after coming on as a substitute for Helder Postiga. "I'm very happy, this is a prize for my players, who have been working very hard," said Sporting coach Paulo Bentom. Shakhtar stay on three points with Basel on one. "It was a balanced game. The experienced Sporting took advantage of some of our mistakes", Shakhtar coach Mircea Lucescu told reporters
